        public void add​(int index,

      • lastExcellentRectangle

        public Rectangle lastExcellentRectangle()
        Finds and returns the LAST excellent rectangle in the array. It returns null if the array has no excellent rectangles. A rectangle is excellent if the following conditions are true y is not 0 and height is not 0 and the remainder of x divided by y equals the remainder of width divided by height The method should stop execution and return the last perfect rectangle after it is found.
        Returns:
        the excellent rectangle
